<h2 id="ID-83ad97c6-0176-4370-bda7-ebb4a1cc64bb">Couchdb&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<span class="tag"><span class="couchdb">couchdb</span></span></h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org47a85ad">
<p>
Couchdb is a Nosql database that offers replication and a simple to use rest api. it is written in erlang.
</p>

<p>
I use couchdb for my project <a href="2022-05-28-030619-star_intel.html#ID-78157cd5-9681-4a64-b5c7-0f2b415cd446">star intel</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-ID-1d8d35c7-e2b3-4c44-864b-6a0f88274c34" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="ID-1d8d35c7-e2b3-4c44-864b-6a0f88274c34">Setup</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-orgc1f50f4">
</div>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a id="ID-e6653e2b-e78e-4eb6-b5ef-679cd0ac589f"></a>Docker&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<span class="tag"><span class="docker">docker</span></span><br />
<div class="outline-text-5" id="text-org7b19a87">
<p>
There is a community made docker container and one made by ibm that bundles FTS.
</p>

<p>
Documentation is <a href="https://hub.docker.com/_/couchdb">here</a>.
</p>

<p>
I run couchdb like this
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-sh"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;"># </span><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">Make a directory to store the database</span>
mkdir $<span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">PWD</span>/db
<span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;"># </span><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">Fix permissions for the database since ibm runs it as uid 1001 and gid 1001</span>
chown 1001:1001 $<span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">PWD</span>/db
<span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;"># </span><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">Run the database</span>
docker run -d  -e <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">COUCHDB_USER</span>=admin -e <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">COUCHDB_PASSWORD</span>=password  -v $<span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">PWD</span>/db:/opt/couchdb/data  -p 0.0.0.0:5984:5984 ibmcom/couchdb3
</pre>
</div>


<p>
After you run it navigate to <a href="http://127.0.0.1/_utils">http://127.0.0.1/_utils</a> and login
Setup the atabse, change the password and it is ready to use.
</p>
